  "analysis": "The previous GenBank parse command produced no visible output, likely because it is still waiting or failed to execute. We still need to inspect plasmid.gb, verify BioPython, and test API access. The input files show 20 PDB IDs and the antibody heavy/light chain sequences.",
  "plan": "Run a compact batch: check Python/BioPython, print plasmid.gb content, parse it with error handling, and test network/API access to RCSB/PDBe/fpbase. This will establish available tools and data needed to identify DHFR, donor/acceptor, and binder proteins.",
